						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1459 (1538)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers a gift of four silver beds to be used as cushions of the swing during the <hi rend="italic">Tiruvūñjal</hi> (swing) festival, by <hi rend="bold">Viśvanātha Nāyaka</hi> on behalf of the king. The weight of these cushions is stated to be 8392 <hi rend="italic">Tūkkam Varāhaṉ</hi> both by <hi rend="italic">Araimaṉaippaḍikkal</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kōyilppaḍikkal.</hi> The details of date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1458, (wrong for 1459) Hēviḷambi, Māśi 12, correspond to 1538 A.D., February 7, but are insufficient for verification.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
